1 d. The number of jobs per year while on parole and the percentage
2 of days employed while on parole; and
3 e. The number of residence changes to a new zip code during
4 parole;
5 6. Prior criminal history, including the number of prior arrests and
6 convictions; and
7 7. Rates of recidivism.
8 (2) The department shall:
9 (a) Collect all data necessary to prepare the report and may promulgate
10 administrative regulations in accordance with KRS Chapter 13A to
11 implement this section; and
12 (b) Make the full report and an executive summary available to the general public
13 on its website[Web site].
14 Section 2. This Act takes effect January 1, 2026.
